Lorica is a fork of Pingora, modified to serve as a dashboard-first
reverse proxy product. The original Pingora source code has been
renamed from pingora-* to lorica-*, with unused components removed
(OpenSSL, BoringSSL, s2n-tls backends, cache subsystem).

Architectural patterns in Lorica are inspired by Sozu (Clever Cloud),
reimplemented from scratch. No Sozu code has been copied (AGPL-3.0
prevents code reuse).
